  "local_port": 42880,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you've lost your Chase debit card. Taking prompt action is crucial to protect your account and prevent unauthorized transactions. Here are the steps you should follow:\n\n### 1. **Report the Lost Card Immediately**\n\n- **By Phone:**\n  - **Chase Customer Service:** Call **1-800-935-9935** to report your lost debit card. This line is typically available 24/7.\n  \n- **Via Mobile App or Online Banking:**\n  - If you have access to the Chase mobile app or online banking, you can report your card as lost or stolen directly through these platforms. Look for options like \"Card Services\" or \"Report Lost Card\" in the menu.\n\n### 2. **Freeze Your Account (If Available)**\n\n- Some banking apps, including Chase\u2019s, offer the option to temporarily freeze your account. This can prevent any unauthorized transactions while you resolve the issue.\n\n### 3. **Review Recent Transactions**\n\n- **Check for Unauthorized Activity:**\n  - Log into your Chase account online or via the mobile app to review recent transactions. If you notice any suspicious or unauthorized charges, report them immediately to Chase.\n\n### 4. **Request a New Debit Card**\n\n- When you report your lost card, request a replacement. Chase typically issues a new debit card within a few business days. Ensure that your mailing address is up to date to receive the new card promptly.\n\n### 5. **Update Automatic Payments and Linked Services**\n\n- **Automatic Payments:**\n  - If your debit card was linked to any automatic payments (utilities, subscriptions, etc.), update these services with your new card information once you receive it to avoid missed payments.\n\n- **Online Accounts:**\n  - Update your debit card details on any online accounts where it's saved for quicker checkouts or bill payments.\n\n### 6. **Monitor Your Account Regularly**\n\n- **Set Up Alerts:**\n  - Enable account alerts through Chase\u2019s mobile app or online banking. You can receive notifications for transactions via email or SMS, helping you stay informed about any activity on your account.\n\n- **Regular Reviews:**\n  - Periodically review your account statements and transaction history to ensure there are no unauthorized activities.\n\n### 7. **Secure Your Personal Information**\n\n- **Protect Your PIN and Passwords:**\n  - Ensure that your PIN and online banking passwords are secure. If you suspect that more personal information was compromised along with your debit card, consider changing your passwords and taking additional security measures.\n\n- **Consider a Fraud Alert:**\n  - If you believe your personal information may have been compromised, consider placing a fraud alert on your credit reports by contacting one of the major credit bureaus (Equifax, Experian, or TransUnion).\n\n### 8. **Stay Vigilant Against Scams**\n\n- **Beware of Phishing Attempts:**\n  - Be cautious of unsolicited calls, emails, or messages claiming to be from Chase asking for personal information. Chase will never ask for sensitive information through these channels.\n\n### **Chase Contact Information:**\n\n- **Customer Service:**  \n  - **Phone:** 1-800-935-9935  \n  - **TTY:** 1-800-935-9936 (for the hearing impaired)\n  \n- **Chase Website:** [www.chase.com](https://www.chase.com)  \n- **Chase Mobile App:** Available on [iOS](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/chase-mobile/id298867247) and [Android](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.chase.sig.android) devices.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Document Your Actions:**\n  - Keep a record of when and how you reported the lost card, including confirmation numbers or names of representatives you spoke with.\n\n- **Follow Up:**\n  - After reporting, monitor your account to ensure that the lost card has been successfully deactivated and that no unauthorized transactions occur.\n\nTaking these steps promptly will help safeguard your account and minimize the risk of unauthorized use. If you have any further concerns or need assistance, don\u2019t hesitate to reach out directly to Chase customer support.",
